casebody.data:
No. -.

Suárez v. Bautista. Appeal from the District Court of San Juan. Motion to dismiss appeal. Decided June 24, 1912. Mr. Francisco Socorro for the moving party. Mr. Ramón Falcon for the adverse party.

Motion overruled for failure to show whether a statement of the case was presented, which is required in order that it may be ascertained whether or not the period allowed by law for the filing of the record had expired.
